label.value: Atypical Endometriosis

value.value: A precancerous lesion characterized by the presence of atypical glandular epithelial features in foci of endometriosis. Atypical endometriosis has been observed in contiguity with carcinomas.

A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q22) of chromosome 10 and the short arm (p13) of chromosome 17. It results in an YWHAE-FAM22 fusion. It has been described in high grade endometrial stromal sarcomas and a subset of clear cell sarcomas of the kidney.

label.value: Endocrine System

value.value: Collective designation for those tissues capable of secreting hormones.

label.value: YWHAE-FAM22 Fusion Protein Expression

value.value: Expression of fusion protein YWHAE-FAM22 transcripts resulting from a t(10;17)(q22;p13). The translocation results in rearrangement of the YWHAE gene on chromosome 17 and FAM22 gene on chromosome 10. It has been described in high grade endometrial stromal sarcomas and a subset of clear cell sarcomas of the kidney.

label.value: Filtered Cigar

value.value: A smaller cigar that is combined with a filter intended to reduce the amount of smoke, tar, and fine particles inhaled.

label.value: Snus

value.value: A moist powder tobacco product that is used by placing it under the upper lip for extended periods.

label.value: Paan with Tobacco

value.value: A combination of betel leaf, areca nut, and tobacco. It is chewed for its stimulant and psychoactive effects.

label.value: Gutka

value.value: A combination of crushed areca nut, tobacco, catechu, paraffin wax, slaked lime, and sweet or savory flavorings. It is placed between the cheek and gum and is a mild stimulant.

label.value: Zarda

value.value: A combination of tobacco, lime, spices, vegetable dyes, and areca nut. It is typically chewed for its stimulant effects.

label.value: Khaini

value.value: A combination of tobacco and slaked lime paste with or without areca nut. It is placed between the cheek and gum and is a mild stimulant.

label.value: YWHAE/FAM22 Fusion Gene

value.value: A fusion gene that results from a chromosomal translocation t(10;17)(q22;p13) which fuses the exon 5 the YWHAE gene with exon 2 of the FAM22A (NUTM2A), FAM22B (NUTM2B), or FAM22E (NUTM2E) gene. These fusions are associated with high grade endometrial stromal sarcomas and clear cell sarcomas of the kidney.

label.value: Uterine Corpus Rhabdomyosarcoma

value.value: A rare malignant heterologous neoplasm with skeletal muscle differentiation arising from the uterine corpus. It usually manifests with vaginal bleeding. The prognosis is poor.

label.value: Smoked at Least 100 Cigarettes in Entire Life

label.value: Endoderm

value.value: The deepest of the three primary germ layers (ectoderm, mesoderm and endoderm) found in the early trilaminar embryo, which forms the epithelial linings of the respiratory and digestive tracts.

label.value: Corneal Endothelium

value.value: A single layer of specialized, flat, mitochondria-rich cells that line the posterior surface of the cornea, which govern fluid and solute transport across the posterior surface of the cornea.

label.value: Smoked Cigarettes During Year Before First Diagnosed with Cancer

label.value: Benign Uterine Corpus PEComa

value.value: A benign neoplasm with perivascular epithelioid cell differentiation arising from the uterine corpus. It is characterized by the absence of pleomorphism and scarcity or absence of mitotic figures. It usually affects perimenopausal women. Patients present with a pelvic mass or abnormal bleeding.

label.value: Uterine Corpus Malignant PEComa

value.value: A malignant neoplasm with perivascular epithelioid cell differentiation arising from the uterine corpus. The neoplasm is usually a large size, and charcaterized by the presence of marked nuclear atypia, pleomorphism, increased mitotic activity, necrosis, and infiltrative margins.  The most common metastatic sites are lungs, lymph nodes, and bone. Patients present with a pelvic mass or abnormal bleeding.

label.value: Uterine Corpus Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: A benign or malignant germ cell tumor that arises from the uterine corpus. Representative examples include teratoma and yolk sac tumor.

label.value: Epidermis

value.value: The epithelial portion of the skin (cutis). It consists of the following layers: stratum corneum (horny layer), stratum granulosum (granular layer), stratum spinosum (prickle cell layer), and stratum basale (basal cell layer).
